On October 29, 1969, UCLA graduate student Charley Kline sent
the first Internet message, trying to log in to a remote Stanford
computer using the new ARPANET network. The connection
crashed after the first two letters — “L” and “O”. These 16 bits went
down in history as the start of the Internet era.
